---
// Tech-stack section. Two adjacent paper cards — one for the languages I
// think in, one for the tools I reach for. Everything visible at rest:
// no marquee, no expand-on-click, no shared bento-card hover lift. The
// `#skills-tools` anchor is preserved on the wrapper so existing nav
// links (Nav.astro, MobileMenu.astro) keep resolving.
//
// Anchor styling — the first item in each row is wrapped in <em>, which
// inherits the editorial italic+accent treatment from global.css. This
// honors the "tools I *actually* reach for" framing without needing a
// dedicated chip variant.
//
// Intentionally avoids the .bento-card / .bento class names: both are
// globally styled with hover lift, pointer cursor, and aspect-ratio
// rules in BentoGrid.astro + global.css. These cards are static.
---

<section id="skills-tools" class="stack-split" aria-label="Technical stack">
  <article class="stack-split-card">
    <h2 class="stack-split-title">Languages I <em>think in</em></h2>
    <p class="stack-split-sub">Code + the ML stack on top.</p>

    <h3>Languages</h3>
    <ul class="stack-chip-row">
      <li class="stack-chip"><em>Python</em></li>
      <li class="stack-chip">C++</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">JavaScript</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">SQL</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Bash</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Swift</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>ML / AI</h3>
    <ul class="stack-chip-row">
      <li class="stack-chip"><em>PyTorch</em></li>
      <li class="stack-chip">TensorFlow</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">TensorRT</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">ONNX</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">OpenCV</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">GStreamer</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Nvidia Jetson</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <article class="stack-split-card">
    <h2 class="stack-split-title">Tools I <em>reach for</em></h2>
    <p class="stack-split-sub">How code becomes a running service.</p>

    <h3>Infra &amp; DevOps</h3>
    <ul class="stack-chip-row">
      <li class="stack-chip"><em>Docker</em></li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Jenkins</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">GitLab CI/CD</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">AWS S3</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Grafana</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">ELK</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Kubernetes</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Frameworks &amp; Tools</h3>
    <ul class="stack-chip-row">
      <li class="stack-chip"><em>Flask</em></li>
      <li class="stack-chip">REST APIs</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">PostgreSQL</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Selenium</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Scrapy</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Postman</li>
      <li class="stack-chip">Git</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</section>

<style>
  .stack-split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  /* Single column below the site's mobile nav breakpoint. Two cards
     side-by-side at 540-640px would be cramped given the 880px page
     max-width and inner padding. */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .stack-split {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .stack-split-card {
    background: var(--paper);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card, 14px);
    padding: 24px 26px;
    color: var(--ink);
    /* No hover lift, no cursor change — these cards aren't interactive. */
  }

  .stack-split-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 1vw + 1rem, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  /* em inside the title inherits italic+accent from the global em rule. */

  .stack-split-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11.5px;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    margin: 6px 0 18px;
  }

  .stack-split-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    margin: 18px 0 8px;
  }
  .stack-split-card h3:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  .stack-chip-row {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
  }
  .stack-chip {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(26, 26, 28, 0.06);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  html.dark .stack-chip {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
  }
  /* Anchor item — uses <em> for the italic+accent treatment, with a
     soft accent-tinted chip bg to lift it off the row. */
  .stack-chip:has(em) {
    background: var(--accent-soft);
  }
</style>
